<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="removable">Removable tags</h3>
<p>Just include a <a href="/close">close</a> button and attach a click handler using your preferred method. Here's a basic example:</p>
<code-sample>
  <script>
    const removeTag = (e, id) => confirm(`Remove tag with id=${id}?`) ? e.currentTarget.parentElement.remove() : null;
  </script>
  <template>
    <h4>Filters</h4>
    <m-tag>bug<m-close onclick="removeTag(event, 1)"></m-close></m-tag>
    <m-tag>open<m-close onclick="removeTag(event, 2)"></m-close></m-tag>
    <m-tag>mine<m-close onclick="removeTag(event, 3)"></m-close></m-tag>
  </template>
</code-sample>

<h3 id="accessibility">Accessibility</h3>
<p>Use <code>aria-label</code> when the Tag only contains an icon:</p>
<code-sample>
  <m-tag aria-label="free breakfast"><m-icon name="cup"></m-icon></m-tag>
</code-sample>

